  "prompt": "I have a flight to prague. But In between I have to change flight at Paris! How to do that?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to navigate a flight connection in Paris:\n\n1. At the first airport:\n- Check your connecting flight details\n- Ask airline staff about connection procedures\n- Get your boarding pass for the next flight\n\n2. At Paris airport (Charles de Gaulle/CDG):\n- Follow signs for connections/transfers\n- Go through transfer/transit area\n- Check departure board for your next flight\n- Go to correct terminal/gate\n\n3. Important tips:\n- Allow enough time between flights (usually 1-2 hours)\n- Check if you need to collect and recheck baggage\n- Have your passport ready\n- Follow airline/airport instructions\n\n4. If connection is tight:\n- Inform airline staff\n- They can help you navigate quickly\n- Might assist with transfer if delayed\n\n5. Potential challenges:\n- Different terminals\n- Immigration procedures\n- Language barriers\n\nSpecific advice depends on:\n- Airlines\n- Airports\n- Your specific route\n\nWould you like me to provide more specific guidance based on your exact flight details?",
